\b Assumptions\b0\par
\pard\li360
\bullet\tab A dedicated QA or staging environment, separate from production, is available.\par
\bullet\tab Dedicated Company1 and Company2 automation accounts exist. Their credentials and API tokens are stored in CI secrets, never in source control.\par
\bullet\tab Test accounts have an approved non-production 2FA mechanism. Production security is never bypassed.\par
\bullet\tab The product exposes stable data-testid attributes or accessible names for important UI controls.\par
\bullet\tab A project created by a test can be deleted through an API endpoint or an approved cleanup process.\par
\bullet\tab Mobile refers to responsive mobile web. If it means a native app, Appium with BrowserStack App Automate is additionally required.\par
\pard\li0\par
\b Part 1 - Debugging Flaky Test Code\b0\par
\par
\b Flakiness issues and fixes\b0\par
\pard\li360
\bullet\tab The URL is asserted immediately after clicking Login. Authentication and navigation are asynchronous. Fix: wait for the dashboard URL with Playwright's expect(page).to_have_url().\par
\bullet\tab is_visible() is checked before dynamic dashboard content is ready. Fix: wait for a dashboard-ready element with expect(locator).to_be_visible().\par
\bullet\tab Project cards are read while the tenant dashboard is still loading. Fix: wait for a projects-list or first project-card locator before inspecting results.\par
\bullet\tab Generic CSS selectors such as #login-btn and .project-card are brittle. Fix: use role, label, or data-testid locators.\par
\bullet\tab There is no explicit 2FA strategy. A user who receives an MFA challenge will not reach the dashboard. Fix: use a controlled test identity or approved test OTP service.\par
\bullet\tab Credentials are hard-coded. Accounts can be locked, changed, or rate-limited. Fix: use dedicated accounts and secret management.\par
\bullet\tab Each test directly manages browser lifetime. A failed assertion can skip later cleanup. Fix: use pytest yield fixtures so context and browser close reliably.\par
\bullet\tab Tests are not parameterized for browser or viewport variation. Fix: use a browser/device CI matrix and fresh context for every test.\par
\bullet\tab Checking only the visible text Company2 is weak tenant validation. Fix: verify a tenant identifier in the UI and use an API authorization test with a second tenant.\par
\pard\li0\par
\b Why it happens more in CI than locally\b0\par
Local machines often have warm caches, fewer competing processes, known browser versions, a consistent screen size, and lower network latency. CI workers can have slower CPU and I/O, cold caches, parallel jobs, browser version differences, different viewports, network delays, and delayed third-party authentication responses. These timing differences expose race conditions caused by immediate assertions. The answer is not arbitrary sleep calls; it is waiting for a meaningful application state.\par
\par
\b Corrected Playwright approach (illustrative code)\b0\par
\pard\f1\fs18
def login(page, email, password):\par
    page.goto(BASE_URL + "/login", wait_until="domcontentloaded")\par
    expect(page.get_by_test_id("login-form")).to_be_visible()\par
    page.get_by_label("Email").fill(email)\par
    page.get_by_label("Password").fill(password)\par
    page.get_by_role("button", name="Sign in").click()\par
    expect(page).to_have_url(re.compile(r".*/dashboard(?:\\?.*)?$"))\par
    expect(page.get_by_test_id("dashboard-ready")).to_be_visible()\par
\par
def test_company2_tenant_context(page, company2_user):\par
    login(page, company2_user["email"], company2_user["password"])\par
    expect(page.get_by_test_id("active-tenant")).to_have_text("Company2")\par
    expect(page.get_by_test_id("projects-list")).to_be_visible()\par
\pard\f0\fs24\par
The repository implements this approach in tests/ui/test_login.py, framework/pages.py, and conftest.py. It uses fixture-based cleanup, configurable timeouts, isolated browser contexts, and device options.\par
